deck_excerpt: A budget Yu-Gi-Oh! deck capable of playing the metagame!
deck_description:
I feel as though the Materiactor engine has been completely overlooked. I, myself, was caught up in finding a deck that wants level 3 normal monsters as part of its engine, but Prima Materiactor changes all of that. Instead, you're left with a tight engine that stacks and adds whatever piece you need to keep your deck moving. 

In virtual world, the level 3 access keeps you in line with the deck's core game-plan while adding a very recursive draw engine with Exgard adding whatever pieces you need back to the hand. Small world is a must have in the deck as any card in the deck is a bridge to any other card in the deck.

deck_name: the true cancer of all worlds
deck_description: cancer

This deck basically focuses on summoning Crooked Cook and winning under Exodia The Forbidden One's effect.

 

If your opponent doesn't have anything that can get rid of Crooked Cook like tribute summoning under the effect of Kaiju or inflicting to your life points under the effect of cards that can do piercing damage or direct attack like Toon Monsters for example, then it's most likely you're going to win by either make them wait longer until you get all parts of Exodia in your hands or they basically just go surrender.

 

So basically you need to summon Crooked Cook using the Right-Hand Shark as an XYZ material and it's required because the effect this monster is if it's used as an XYZ material, the XYZ monster will automatically gain that can't be destroyed by battle and by the passive effect of Crooked Cook it will be indestructible unless your opponent uses it as a material for a tribute summon.

 

This is just a troll deck and just an experiment but for some reason it still kinda works.

deck_excerpt: Final Countdown Win ft. World + Chaos Beast + Carbon
deck_description:
Greetings! Once upon a time, I made this deck thanks to Princess and win with Final Countdown. Now, I did it with Chaos Beast instead because what if Princess is banned? Let's find out.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Bring forth Tethys by replacing Capricious/Aces/Corobane and draw your whole deck...

  • Whenever you draw a Fairy, reveal it to draw another card with Tethys. You can keep it going until you can't draw anymore.
  • If you hit non-Fairy, you stop movement. So, continue with Ixchel and alike to trigger Tethys again.
  • Always use "Arcana Force XV" in-hand to fetch what would be otherwise brick by Tethys, which is "Light Barrier".
  • Know that card draw has to be caused by an effect, not as cost, in order to draw a card with Tethys. For example, using "Upstart Goblin", seen in Side Deck, won't do any help for Tethys but "Into the Void" will. Remember this rule well.

2) If Tethys + Aces are together, Link Summon Insulator with them. Otherwise, place Rain and Lebellman onto Pendulum Zones to Pendulum Summon 2 x Carbon + Capricious + Orange. Also, activate "Final Countdown" and "Light Barrier".

3) XYZ Summon Starring Knight with 2 x Carbon as materials. Then, use Knight to Special Summon The World and pick the outcome as heads thanks to "Light Barrier" to be able to skip your opponent's turn by sending two monsters you control to GY.

4) Synchro Summon Chaos Beast with Capricious + Orange. At that moment, Carbon asks you to shuffle itself on top of your Main Deck, which is essential to not deck-out for 20 turns forward.

5) End your turn and use The World to send Beast + Knight to GY, in order to be able to do what was explained in #3. When it's your move, bring forth Carbon + Beast for The World and repeat until you win with Final Countdown...

  • With many LIGHT and DARK monsters available at your arsenal, reviving Beast won't be an issue, provided that you use Beast to retrieve banished monsters into your hand. Afterwards, Pendulum Summon them and use these as resources for The World.
  • No matter what you do, don't forget to send Carbon to GY for The World at all costs to not deck-out by accident.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Into The Void" can be found either within "The Infinite Void" or "Life Force Control System" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Darklord Ixchel" can be found either within "The Opening Act of an Apocalypse" or "Deceitful Wings of Darkness" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Trickstar Corobane" can be found within "Essence of Flora and Ocean" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Tokusano Shinkyojin" can be found within "Crystal Realm Defier" Secret Pack to save 90 UR!

- "Chicken Game" can be found within "The Most Dangerous Race of the Cosmos!" Secret Pack to save 90 UR!

- "Final Countdown" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 30 UR!

- "World Soul - Carbon" can be found either within "Hope Sprouting in the Spring Breeze" or "The Ones Who Serve Ra" Secret Packs to save 60 SR!

- "Arcana Force XXI - The World" + "Light Barrier" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR and 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 360 SR and 240 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Finalized deck list after much testing
deck_description:
My last deck list for Live☆Twin Fiendsmith Unchained kinda popped off even though it was just a rough draft, and I have spent all week testing this deck to find what new innovations i could bring to the list, so I just wanted to share this list and my thoughts about the deck.

First major change I made was removing an engraver and a tract. This was simply too much for the main deck fiendsmith cards. Being able to turn the Ki-sikil link monsters makes the extra fiendsmith cards not as neccesary because of how easy it is to make requiem in hands that dont have any fiendsmith cards in them.

Next change i made was removing the Abominable Unchained Soul. there really wasnt a reason to include it in the deck, it almost never came up and there are better cards to search with Yama or the unchained spell, it also doesnt have the ability to make Caesar unlike the other good unchained cards.

With this newfound space in the deck I was able to slot in 3 imperms. Having ash blossom as the only handtrap was a major throw. The deck is able to play through interuption pretty well, but it definetly struggles against a fully formed end board that i wasnt able to stop because i didnt draw a handtrap.

A minor change I made was removing 1 Lil-la from the main deck for a Ki-sikil Frost. Normaling Frost can also act as a starter just like normal Ki-sikil (albeit a weaker one.) Also, having Frost in your hand when your normal summon Lil-la gets interrupted, or searching it with sunny snitch when you already opened a Live☆Twin. The utility of this card is definetly something i looked over when I was building the original deck.

The final change I made was taking a solemn out of the side deck for a copy of the big Evil★Twin main deck monster. At one point during testing I was struggling to find a way the deck could get over larger monsters. Something that worried me was my opponent making a giant unaffected tower that i had no out for. This was my best solution for that. I think that 4400ATK was plenty and you only need one copy of it because Trouble Sunny gives quick access to it paired with non-destroying non-targeting removal.

If I you have any questions, please feel free to ask in the comments. I check my decks often, so I will most likely respond.

A new semi-splashable Yugioh engine has hit the block, and its themes of Biblical creation and angelic imagery one of the best designs I've seen in this game to date! YCS Providence was this strategy's first major event to perform on the big stage, and it actually reached top 32! Inspired by Steven Wind's top 32 YCS Providence list, this Regenesis deck uses Kashtira and Fiendsmith cards to enable it to outresource opponents in simplified gamestates (all too common nowadays with everydeck sporting 15+ handtraps)!
 
The deck is very simple to play, so I'm not making a detailed strategy guide on it. Basically, you bait interruption with your Kashtira/Fiendsmith cards, then you set-up with your Regenesis monsters! If you end up getting negated a lot, remember that any 2 monsters is full Fiendsmith combo thanks to Moon of the Closed Heaven.
 
Regenesis basically ends at minimum with a "book of the moon" flip face down effect with Regenesis Birth - or if your graveyard/banished has a lot of Regenesis in it, you can summon them en-masse. The basic combo is Regenesis Archfiend -> Regenesis -> Regenesis Lord -> Summons itself banishing Archfiend then sets Birth from deck. This interruption seems relatively little, but augmented by Fiendsmith, Kashtira and handtraps, it can be difficult for your opponent to face, especially since all three engines recur everyturn. This deck also has 12 handtraps/staple slots, making it easier to play 1st and second. You can also beat over monsters relatively easily, since most monsters in this deck are freely summoned and have 2000+ ATK.

The Extra Deck are mostly cards for the Fiendsmith deck, and can be changed anytime to suit your playstyle. Honestly, this deck can do without the entire Fiendsmith package and can be played purely with Kashtira! The Extra Deck can be used as fodder for Pot of Extravagance or Super Polymerization in that deckbuild.

Kashtira and Regenesis also has the funny distinction of having their ace cards named "Birth" so you can call this deck "double birth control!" Thought that was pretty funny. xD

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

deck_excerpt: Use the radioactive power of the Materiactor cards to turbo rank 3s and search for hand traps from the deck!
deck_description: Couple different engines - Materiactor of course but also some goblin biker for added consistency/disruption with gabonga, and psychic level 3s to extend and play through hand traps

The hand is mightier than the field.
In Domain Format, it's commonly believed that handtraps are rare due to the 60-card deckbuilding requirement. Today, we’re turning that idea on its head—with a deck where two-thirds of the cards are handtraps.

Deckmaster: Wish Dragon 
Domain Restriction: LIGHT // EARTH // DRAGON 
Made for Domain Format: Join the Community Discord!

Domain Format General Rules:

  • Singleton Format: Every card restricted to 1 copy per deck.
  • 60-card Format: Each Main Deck must contain exactly 60 cards.
  • 4-player Pods: Each player competes individually in an all-out battle against three opponents.
  • Deckmaster Restrictions: Each player chooses a "Deckmaster" which dictates the allowed types and attributes for their deck.
  • Deckmaster Contract: A Deckmaster can be summoned from a designated "Deckmaster Zone" using normal summoning rules. After switching zones, Deckmasters may return to the "Deckmaster Zone," where they start the game.

Refer here for additional rules and exceptions:

https://www.domainformat.com/rules 

Broad Categories

This simple strategy has cards that fall into 2 broad categories:

  • Handtrap Negates
  • Hooligan Beatsticks

What do we want our Deckmaster to do? Wish Dragon 
- Wide Domain
- Half of a Hieratic Seal of the Heavenly Spheres or Moon of the Closed Heaven 
- Small Defensive Wall

Wish Dragon has the ability to tribute itself in order to summon 2 lv1 Dragon Tokens with no atk/def. This ability additionally locks us from summoning monsters from the extra deck, since we have no lv5 or higher Dragons in the Extra Deck. What this ability provides however, is a little defensive wall that our opponents will have to destroy before they can hurt our lifepoints. 

Wish Dragon is not the best monster in the game, however it does have a perfect domain for this type of deck - wide enough to reach most handtraps while still being easily summonable. Being normal summonable, we can combine it with any other monster in order to summon our powerful link-2s. 

Handtraps
- Negates
- Battle Faders
- Free Summons

Handtraps are the core of the deck, however due to reaching for quantity rather than quality, this deck suffers from many bad conditional and weak handtraps. Regardless however, a hand of 5 can expect to sample 3 handtraps from our pool, and with those 3 handtraps hopefully stop the most problematic combos. 

The goal of this deck is to handtrap and beat them up, so to that point, the player must be aware of the opponent's choke points so that after the handtrap they can never perform the combo again. The power of handtraps is their life in the hand rather than the field, making your opponent's boardbreakers ineffective in preventing you from stopping their combos. 

The Battle Faders of the deck help us stay alive - due to the nature of handtraps our field will be empty most times except for the 2 tokens that our deckmaster Wish Dragon provides. 
Remember that a lot of handtraps are also conditional on an empty field. 

PSY-Framegear monsters require a PSY-Frame Driver, but will banish the PSY-Frame Driver after use. To solve this problem, we play Primite Fusion and Branded Regained (with PSY-Framelord Lambda) to shuffle the PSY-Frame Driver back from banishment into deck. 
Bystial monsters are extremely powerful, especially in conjuction with The Bystial Lubellion ability to search Branded Regained to complete a stream of constant resource generation.  

Beatsticks
- Free Summon
- Clean up the board

Since our Deckmaster Wish Dragon does not provide much attack on their own, we resort to adding monsters in the Main Deck that can presssure our opponent's life points after we have caused them to fail their combos. This deck is rather low to the ground. 

These Beatsticks summon themselves for free, and thus can also be used as half of a Moon of the Closed Heaven for Fiendsmith lines. 
Fiendsmith is our most vaulable extra deck pieces due to thier recusrivibility. Fiendsmith's Rextremende is particularly high attack mosnter that can cause trouble for our opponents. Please note that Fiendsmith Engraver will not be able to discard itself from hand, due to the deck having no Fiendsmith spell/traps. 

Other Considerations: 

Handtraps: Supply Soldier of the Indestructible Insects , Conbirdable , Sauravis, the Ancient and Ascended , Mahaama the Fairy Dragon , Herald of Orange Light 

Monsters: Chaos Dragon Levianeer , Fossil Dyna Pachycephalo , Hugin the Runick Wings , First of the Dragons , Regenesis Lord 

Deckmasters: Koa'ki Meiru Beetle , Justice of Prophecy , Propa Gandake 

The duels not over - it never began.

deck_excerpt: ALIN Ancient Fairy Dragon Support v2 list
deck_description:
I have been refining this deck since my last list. (If you're interested, here it is: https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/luna-invoked-597401)

With a suggestion from the comment on my last list, (thank you TheDragon56) I have added Pot of Prosperity and Set Rotation.  These cards are natural additions to this deck and help consistency immensely.

Additionally, I have added Chicken Game as pretty much an Upstart Goblin that also sets field spell.  I have also added Multi-Universe, an insane card that fixes the main combo's issue of not being able to use Ancient Fairy Dragon's field spell pop without compromising Ancient Fairy Life Dragon's search.  Now, you can use AFD to pop World of Spirits, search Multi-Universe, and activate it to replace World of Spirits and giving it protection from backrow hate.  I also added Junk Speeder as a way to get to your level 8 bosses with Kuribon the Fairy Spirit and Regulus the Fairy Beast if Regulus's search gets interupted.  I added Black Rose Moonlight Dragon as another level 7 boss monster that you can go lv4 body + Revolution Synchron into.  I also cut down on a copy of Ancient Fairy Life Dragon as it doesn't come up as often as I'd like.

I also shifted around the non-engine to be more optimal.  I added Solemn Judgment over Solemn Strike because I feel having more counters to board breakers against your Eternal Sunshine and Ancient Fairy Life Dragon is more helpful for the gameplan.

Potential changes and additions we should look out for are:
1. Running a second Spore the Fairy Seed to deal with Bystials ruining your combo.
2. Synchro Rumble as revival and protection for your boss monsters. 
3. Potentially running Crimson Dragon.


I would love to hear all your thoughts and additions on the deck!

Cheers!

Step into a shadowy realm where ancient forests whisper secrets and cunning witches weave their enchantments! This isn't just a deck; it's a thrilling fairy tale spun from the threads of the White Forest and the wicked allure of the Sinful Spoils. Unleash a symphony of spellcasting with the Spellbook lineage, while the enigmatic White Forest monsters stalk the shadows, ready to pounce with unexpected power. Diabellze and her sinister sisters sow chaos, entwining their dark magic with the forest's ancient guardians. But beware! This idyllic woodland holds a darker edge. The forbidden power of the Sinful Spoils offers tantalizing shortcuts and devastating plays, tempting you to walk a perilous path. Will you succumb to their allure, or will the steadfast protectors of the White Forest guide you to victory? Unravel intricate combos that summon colossal dragons from the depths of the Extra Deck, including the majestic Azamina Moa Regina and the formidable Swordsoul Supreme Sovereign - Chengying. Disrupt your opponent's strategies with well-timed negations and cunning traps, all while weaving a narrative of light and shadow on the dueling field. This deck isn't just about winning; it's about the story you tell with every card played. Are you ready to delve into the mysteries of the White Forest and embrace the power of the Sinful Spoils? Only the most cunning duelists will survive this enchanting and treacherous adventure!

Behold! This isn't your grandma's tea party... unless your grandma summons colossal dragons that warp reality! This Dragonmaid deck blends the adorable charm of hospitality with the ferocious power of draconic destruction. One moment you're tidying up with your Maidens, the next you're unleashing the chaos of Light and Darkness Dragon or banishing foes with the encroaching Bystials. Prepare for a whirlwind of transformations and strategic shifts. We juggle adorable daily duties with the earth-shattering might of Dragon's Mirror and the cunning of Branded magic. Summon your ultimate Dragonmaid Sheou to lock down the board, or unleash the devastating Light End and Dark End Dragons to obliterate your opponent's defenses. With the Bystials adding a disruptive edge and Hieratic Seal of the Heavenly Spheres providing crucial negates, this deck offers a unique blend of control and explosive power. Don't underestimate the cuteness – it's just a clever disguise for the draconic storm brewing within! Are you ready to serve up a side of pure annihilation?

Prepare to witness the fusion of raw power and insidious darkness! This isn't just a Cyber Dragon deck; it's a Kaiju-fueled, Cyberdark-infused engine of destruction, piloted by the regal Therion "King" Regulus. Unleash colossal Kaiju upon your opponent's strongest threats, then seamlessly pivot into a relentless barrage of Cyber Dragons, bolstered by the sinister Cyberdark arsenal. Imagine the satisfying crunch of Jizukiru devouring a problematic monster, paving the way for a devastating Cyberdark End Dragon or the explosive might of Cyber End Dragon. Utilize the cunning of Cyberdark Chimera to fuse with your banished Cyber Dragons, unleashing the multi-attacking fury of Chimeratech Rampage Dragon. But the shadows hold their own terrifying secrets. Cyberdark Realm and Cyberdark Inferno fuel a relentless search for your key Cyberdark monsters and spells, while Cyberdark Invasion can snatch victory from the jaws of defeat. With the strategic use of Clockwork Night, even your opponent's machines can become fuel for your Cyberdark ambitions. This deck isn't just about brute force; it's about calculated aggression and exploiting your opponent's weaknesses. Ash Blossom and Infinite Impermanence stand guard, while Pot of Desires and Cyber Emergency ensure your hand is always primed for action. So, are you ready to command the fusion of light and darkness? To obliterate your foes with Kaiju might and the relentless evolution of Cyber Dragons, all while wielding the shadowy power of the Cyberdarks? This deck offers a unique and thrilling path to victory – are you bold enough to take it?

Step into a realm where twilight meets oblivion! This isn't your grandma's Lightsworn – we've plunged into the abyss and emerged with a chaotic symphony of light and darkness. Unleash devastating dragons born from the very fabric of chaos, fueled by the relentless milling power of Lightsworn and the banishing might of Necroface. Witness: Judgment Day on Demand: The ultimate arbiter, Judgment Dragon, stands ready to cleanse the field in a flash of incandescent light. Chaotic Rebirth: Levianeer and The Chaos Creator rise from the banished, bringing forth overwhelming force. Dimension-Shifting Mayhem: Disrupt your opponent's strategies while fueling your own chaotic engine. Synchro Summons from the Shadows: Explode into powerful Synchro monsters like Chaos Angel and the formidable Swordsoul Supreme Sovereign - Chengying. The Ever-Present Threat of Minerva: Multiple iterations of this Lightsworn prodigy ensure relentless draw power and explosive Extra Deck plays. This deck dances on the edge of control and chaos, offering a unique and exhilarating gameplay experience. Are you ready to embrace the duality and unleash the true power of light and shadow?

Prepare to ensnare your opponents in a web of cunning and deception! This isn't your garden-variety Traptrix deck; it's a venomous viper's nest where the innocent beauty of the Traptrix hides a sinister secret. We've twisted the classic trap strategy, injecting it with the ancient power of the Apophis and Anubis! Imagine your opponent confidently striding into your field, only to be ambushed not just by the treacherous Trap Holes and the alluring Traptrix, but by living traps that slither onto the field as formidable monsters! Embodiment of Apophis and Apophis the Swamp Deity blur the lines between trap and monster, catching your foe completely off guard. And when the scales truly tip, the formidable Anubis the Last Judge and Verdict of Anubis stand ready to deliver a swift and merciless judgment, punishing their every misstep. But the surprises don't end there! The shadowy influence of The Man with the Mark and the disruptive power of cards like Dominus Impulse and Dominus Purge add layers of control and disruption your opponent won't see coming. And for those moments when you need to strike from the shadows, the Extra Deck boasts not only the classic Traptrix powerhouses like Traptrix Sera and Traptrix Rafflesia, but also the colossal Divine Serpent Apophis and the ultimate dragonic threat, Five-Headed Dragon! This deck isn't just about setting traps; it's about crafting an intricate and unpredictable battlefield where your opponent's every move could be their last. Are you ready to unleash the ancient serpents and deliver a truly unforgettable trap experience?

Step into the grand, yet treacherous, Silver Castle! This isn't your average Labrynth build; we've twisted the opulent halls with the shadowy allure of Diabellstar and her Sinful Spoils. Lure your opponent into a web of disruptive traps and cunning hand traps, orchestrated by the elegant Lady and Lovely Labrynth. But beware, for this castle hides more than just welcome mats. Unleash the unexpected might of the Azamina family, morphing and evolving in the Extra Deck to deliver devastating blows and control the flow of battle. From the regal Moa Regina to the shadowy Mu Rcielago, their presence adds a unique and powerful dimension to the Labrynth strategy. Fool your foes with Metalfoes Fusion and the Sinful Spoils package, loading your Graveyard for explosive plays with Transaction Rollback and the ever-present threat of Eradicator Epidemic Virus. With Evenly Matched to reset the board and Infinite Impermanence to stifle your opponent's every move, you'll be the true master of this labyrinthine encounter. Prepare for a Labrynth experience unlike any other – where beauty and brutality intertwine, and the unexpected reigns supreme. Will you extend a Big Welcome, or will your opponent find themselves lost in the castle's intricate and deadly design?

deck_excerpt: Deck de Dark World – Domine as Sombras e Domine o Duelo!  O Dark World é um deck sombrio e poderoso que se aproveita do descarte de cards pa
deck_description:
Deck de Dark World – Domine as Sombras e Domine o Duelo!

O Dark World é um deck sombrio e poderoso que se aproveita do descarte de cards para desencadear efeitos devastadores. Originário do reino das trevas, esse arquétipo gira em torno de monstros que ganham efeitos quando descartados por efeito de card, seja da sua mão ou do deck, transformando um aparente revés em uma vantagem avassaladora.

Principais Estratégias:

  • Descarte Agressivo: Cards como "Broww, Huntsman of Dark World", "Snoww, Unlight of Dark World" e "Reino das Trevas" permitem recuperar recursos e acelerar seu jogo.

  • Controle e Pressão: Monstros como "Grapha, Dragon Lord of Dark World" retornam do Cemitério para destruir cards do oponente e gerar vantagem.

  • Combos Explosivos: Cards como "The Gates of Dark World" e "Dark World Dealings" aceleram seu engine, enquanto "Ceruli, Guru of Dark World" e "Sillva, Warlord of Dark World" causam estragos ao serem descartados pelo adversário.

Por Que Jogar Dark World?

✔ Recuperação de Recursos: Quanto mais você descarta, mais seu campo se fortalece.
✔ Versatilidade: Funciona bem em formatos como Tcg, Master Duel e Duel Links.
✔ Potencial de OTK: Com os combos certos, você pode eliminar o oponente em um único turno!

Se você gosta de um estilo de jogo agressivo e cheio de reviravoltas, o Dark World é a escolha perfeita! Domine as trevas e reduza seus adversários a pó!

Dark World – Onde o Descarte é Apenas o Começo da Sua Vitória!

Prepare to unleash a tempest of feathers and fury! This isn't your grandma's Harpie deck – it's a whirlwind of Simorgh synergy, soaring to new heights with the cunning of the Mist Valley and the relentless aggression of their winged allies. Weave through a storm of Harpie Ladies, each a vital piece in a symphony of destruction, while the enigmatic Simorghs manipulate the winds to summon colossal threats and disrupt your opponent's every move. From the explosive potential of "Harpie's Feather Duster" to the lockdown power of "Harpie's Feather Storm," this deck commands the skies. Utilize the search power of "Harpie Harpist" and "Harpie Perfumer" to assemble your avian armada, then launch into devastating combos with "Harpie Channeler" and "Elegant Egotist." The strategic placement of "Harpies' Hunting Ground" and "Elborz, the Sacred Lands of Simorgh" will keep your opponent on edge, while "Simorgh Onslaught" and "Dominus Impulse" pave the way for overwhelming board presence. But the true brilliance lies in the seamless integration of the Simorghs. "Simorgh, Bird of Bringing" and "Simorgh, Bird of Beginning" ensure consistent resource gathering, while "Simorgh, Bird of Perfection" and "Simorgh, Bird of Protection" offer crucial disruption and resilience. When the time is right, unleash the might of "Simorgh of Darkness" and "Simorgh, Lord of the Storm" to dominate the field. The Extra Deck is a flexible arsenal, ready to adapt to any challenge. "Cyber Slash Harpie Lady" provides swift removal and further strengthens your Harpie strategy, while the Rank 4 toolbox offers versatile options like "Number 41: Bagooska the Terribly Tired Tapir" and "Lightning Chidori." For those game-ending pushes, "Accesscode Talker" stands ready to deliver the final blow, guided by the strategic prowess of "Harpie Conductor." This isn't just a deck; it's an aerial assault, a masterclass in resource management, and a testament to the combined might of the Harpies and the Simorghs. Soar above the competition and leave your opponents in the dust – the storm is coming!
Bonk energy.

Gaze upon a tapestry woven with the very essence of dragonic might! This is no mere collection of cards; it's a symphony of sapphire scales and thunderous roars, a relentless storm led by the peerless Blue-Eyes White Dragon and its formidable lineage. From the enigmatic depths of the Primite dragons, echoing with ancient power, to the celestial heights commanded by Synchro and Fusion behemoths, this deck surges with overwhelming force.

Harness the arcane synergy between the White Stones and the wisdom of the Sages, igniting a chain reaction that floods the field with azure brilliance. Bend reality with the forbidden rituals of Chaos MAX Dragon and the primal fusion of ancient dragons. With cards like "The Melody of Awakening Dragon" and "Trade-In," the path to summoning your ultimate dragons is swift and decisive.

But be warned, this is not a strategy for the faint of heart. It demands a duelist who can command the tempest, who can weave through disruption with "Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring" and "Infinite Impermanence," and who can seize victory with the devastating might of dragons that pierce the heavens.

Prepare to witness the legend reborn. Prepare to unleash the Azure Onslaught!
